<%# locals: (visits: "", last_ack: "") %>
<h1>Filters demo</h1>

<p>
  This action wires up <code>before_action</code>, <code>after_action</code>,
  and a <code>handle</code>/<code>super</code> "around" filter on
  <code>Fresco::Action</code>.
</p>

<dl>
  <dt><strong>before_action</strong></dt>
  <dd>Increments a session-tracked visit counter on every request.
      Visits so far: <code><%= visits %></code>.</dd>

  <dt><strong>after_action</strong></dt>
  <dd>Stamps <code>filter_last_ack</code> in the session with the
      visit count it just saw. Because <em>after_action</em> runs after
      the response body is built, the value below is the count from
      your <em>previous</em> visit — refresh and it'll catch up.
      Last ack: <code><%= last_ack %></code>.</dd>

  <dt><strong>around (handle + super)</strong></dt>
  <dd>Measures elapsed micros for the whole pipeline and logs it to
      the server stdout. Check your <code>bin/dev</code> terminal for
      a <code>[filters] /filters took …us</code> line.</dd>
</dl>

<h2>Try the halt</h2>
<p>
  <a href="/filters?halt=1">Hit /filters?halt=1</a> — <code>before_action</code>
  will <code>halt!</code> with a flash redirect back to <code>/filters</code>
  without ever running <code>#call</code> or <code>#after_action</code>.
  (The visit counter still ticks up, since <em>before_action</em>
  increments it before the halt check.)
</p>
